ason=The footnote says the building increased to this height in 2003-4|date=September 2018}} || {{convert|55|m|abbr=on}} ||align=center| 14 || 220 [[Greenhill Road, Adelaide|Greenhill Road]] ||align=center| 6\n|-\n|1934\u20131960 || Colonial Mutual Life Building || {{convert|52|m|abbr=on}} ||align=center| 14 || 41-49 [[King William Street, Adelaide|King William Street]] ||align=center| 26\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|South Australia|Architecture}}\n*[[List of tallest buildings in Australia]]\n*[[List of tallest buildings in Oceania]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [http://skyscrapercenter.com/create.php?search=yes&page=0&type_building=on&status_COM=on&status_UC=on&status_UCT=on&status_OH=on&status_NC=on&status_PRO=on&status_VIS=on&status_DEM=on&list_continent=&list_country=&list_city=AU-ADL&list_height=&list_company=&completionsthrough=on&list_year==The Skyscraper Center] (Detailed information on specific buildings)\n* [http://www.emporis.com/en/wm/ci/bu/sk/li/?id=100507&bt=2&ht=2&sro=1 Emporis.com] (General database of skyscrapers)\n* [http://www.sensational-adelaide.com/forum/viewforum.php?f=7 Sensational-Adelaide] (Renders and details of buildings){{user-generated inline |certain=yes|date=April 2019}}\n\n{{Australia tallest buildings lists}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tallest buildings in Adelaide}}\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Adelaide]]\n[[Category:Skyscrapers in Adelaide| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of tallest buildings in Australia|Adelaide]]\n[[Category:Adelaide-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:WestpacHouseAdelaide.jpg|thumb|332x332px|[[Adelaide]]'s tallest building from 1988 until 2019, [[Westpac House]]]]\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=April 2015}}\nThis '''list of tallest buildings in Adelaide''' ranks the tallest buildings in [[Adelaide]], [[South Australia]] by height.  Frome Central Tower 1 (at 11-27 [[Frome Street, Adelaide|Frome Street]]) reached {{convert|135|m|0}} on 1 November 2019, becoming the city's tallest building on that date, although construction is not fully completed yet {{as of|lc=yes| February 2020}}.<ref name=elite>{{cite web | title=Adelaide\u2019s tallest building celebrates 'topping out' | website=Elite Agent | date=3 November 2019 | url=https://eliteagent.com/adelaides-tallest-building-celebrates-topping-out/ | access-date=18 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Adelaidean\">{{cite news |url=https://www.facebook.com/watch/?v=542255806605236 |work=[[Nine News]] |publisher=[[Nine Entertainment Co.]] |title=Adelaide has a new tallest building |date=1 November 2019 |via=Facebook.com|access-date=1 November 2019}}</ref> From its construction in 1988 until late 2019, the tallest building in Adelaide was the 31-[[storey]] [[Westpac House]], which rises {{convert|132|m|0}}, and still {{as of|lc=yes| February 2020}} the tallest completed building. \n\nHeight restrictions, enforced since the 1990s, have limited the number of [[high-rise building]]s constructed in the city, although they have been eased in recent times.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Taller buildings will revitalise the city centre, says John Rau|first=Daniel|last=Wills|url=http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/archive/real-estate/taller-buildings-will-revitalise-the-city-centre-says-john-rau/story-e6frefgc-1226262323868|work=[[The Advertiser (Adelaide)|The Advertiser]]|date=3 February 2012|accessdate=23 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Tallest buildings==\n[[File:Adelaide CBD developments.jpg|thumb|250px|Conservatory on Hindmarsh on the corner of [[Grenfell Street]] and [[Hindmarsh Square]] in the [[Adelaide city centre]].]]\n[[File:Looking south towards adelaide CBD.jpg|thumb|247x247px|Looking south towards the [[Adelaide]] CBD.]]\nThis is a list of the 50 tallest buildings in [[Adelaide]].  Heights are measured to the structural height, which includes architectural elements, but not communications spires or [[Antenna (radio)|antennas]].\n\nHeights are listed to the roof of the building only.\n\n{{legend|#FFE87F|Construction ongoing but height reached|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Rank !! Name{{\\}}Street Address !! Height (m) !! Floors !! Built !! Use !! Street Address\n|- style=\"background:#FFE87F;\"\n|1\n|Adelaidean\n|align=center|138<ref>{{cite news |url=https://invest.cityofadelaide.com.au/blog/koomo-restaurant-will-be-adelaides-highest-cbd-diner-when-it-opens-in-crowne-plaza/ |title=Koomo restaurant will be Adelaide\u2019s highest CBD diner when it opens in Crowne Plaza |first=Gordon |last=Knight |newspaper=Delicious South Australia |date=11 March 2020 |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n|align=center|37\n|2019\n|Mixed Use\n|11-27 Frome Street\n|- style=\"background:#FFE87F;\"\n|2\n|Realm Adelaide\n|align=center|132\n|align=center|40\n|2020\n|Residential\n|9-19 Austin Street\n|-\n|2\n|[[Westpac House]]\n|align=center|132\n|align=center|31\n|1988\n|Commercial Office\n|91 [[King William Street, Adelaide|King William Street]]\n|-\n|4\n|[[Telstra House]]\n| align=\"center\" |104\n| align=\"center\" |24\n|1987\n|Commercial Office\n|30 [[Pirie Street]]\n|-\n|5\n|Kodo Apartments\n|align=center|103<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/business/sa-business-journal/kodo-is-a-step-closer-to-becoming-adelaides-tallest-apartment-tower/news-story/96156c7c1426766051ca9097448ea3e5 |title=Construction on Kodo apartment tower reaches highest point, becomes Adelaide\u2019s tallest residential tower \u2014 for now |first=Giuseppe |last=Tauriello |newspaper=The Advertiser |date=13 November 2018 |accessdate=13 November 2018}}</ref>\n|align=center|30\n|2018\n|Residential\n|27-31 Angas Street\n|-\n|5\n|[[Grenfell Centre]]\n| align=\"center\" |103\n| align=\"center\" |26\n|1975\n|Commercial Office\n|25 [[Grenfell Street]]\n<!-- Please don't add the Mighty Black Stump to this, it's just one podcast and not noteworthy. -->\n|-\n|7\n|[[115 King William Street]]\n|align=center|91\n|align=center|26\n|2016\n|Commercial Office\n|115 [[King William Street, Ade